listing.overview: Agile Tools by Corrello allows you to add story points, WIP Limits and track card time in list.
listing.description:
Agile Tools by Corrello allows you to add story points, WIP Limits and track card time in list. It is fully integrated with [Corrello](https://getcorrello.com?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup) **[burndowns](https://getcorrello.com/Burndown?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_burndown)**, **[CFDs](https://getcorrello.com/cumulative-flow-diagram?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_cfd)**, **burnups**, and **[cycle time](https://getcorrello.com/cycle-time?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_cycletime)** charts.

**Features:**

 - Story points on Cards
 - One click migration of points from Scrum for Trello
 - WIP limits
-  Count of Cards (or points) in each List
 - Card time in list
 - Slow card highlighting

Check out [Corrello](https://getcorrello.com?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=plugin) - Dashboards for Agile teams using Trello.

**Got questions?** drop us a line agiletoolspowerup@getcorrello.com

What are people saying about Agile Tools?
-----

*Software development is a messy process, planning is continuous and new Trello cards get added by the team on a daily basis. It is great to be able to **spot all unestimated cards with one click** and keep the scrum board estimated at all times. It is also extremely useful to get an **overview of the amount of points currently allocated in each Trello column**. This feature comes very handy when trying to understand whether we're putting too much work on our shoulders for our next sprint or whether it's possible to increase our scope.*
- Valentino Giudice (PM **Natural Cycles**)

listing.overview: Visualize Trello cards in a calendar view.
listing.description:
Bring perspective to due dates with the Calendar Power-Up for Trello. Whether you are planning a conference, managing an editorial calendar, or organizing a family vacation, the Calendar Power-Up lets you display cards with due dates in a weekly or monthly calendar view. Easily prioritize cards by dragging and dropping them on the calendar to automatically update their due dates, and export your Trello calendar to third party apps with an iCalendar link.

- Display and filter cards with due dates in a weekly or monthly calendar view.

- Manage due dates by dragging and dropping cards on the calendar.

- Easily see completed tasks by marking due dates complete.

- Export a boards calendar to third party calendars with each boards unique iCalendar link.

- The Calendar Power-Up is supported on the web and iOS and Android mobile devices.

listing.overview: Access all of your Drive files for a project directly from its Trello card, or create and automatically attach new Drive files from a card.
listing.description:
The Google Drive Power-Up for Trello brings your files and folders to Trello cards. Search Google Drive right from Trello and attach relevant files and folders. See real-time previews and details and click back into Google Drive. It also lets you turn your Trello board into a Google Slides presentation with one click.

- Built in file search lets you attach folders and files from Google Drive to a Trello card on any version of Trello.
- See real-time information and previews for any Google Drive files or folders attached to cards.
- Turn your Trello board into a Google Slides presentation with one click.

cards.name: A. As a developer, I want to conduct preliminary research on the video editing mobile application platform so that we understand the requirements.

cards.desc:
Acceptance criteria: 
- Obtained customer expectations on a mobile application.
- Determined the business objectives of the platform.
- Constructed the first Conceptual Model of the platform.
cards.name: B. As a developer, I want to perform contextual analysis so that we can determine the product requirements and construct a conceptual model for a video editing application.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- Completed 80% of the required functionalities into the prototype that needs to be tested.
cards.name: C. As a developer, I want to create a low-fidelity prototype based on the results of the conceptual design process so that user testings can be conducted for further analysis.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- Complete at least 5 user testings.
- Record responses and time taken to complete a task.
cards.name: D. As a developer, I want to perform user testings on our low-fidelity prototype so that we understand user needs and expectations on a deeper level.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
1) Research libraries that our competitors used and evaluate their performance.
2) Several libraries are compared and have their advantages and disadvantages analysed.
cards.name: E. As a developer, I want to conduct research on suitable libraries to be applied for developing our application.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- The platform is able to accept up to ten video clips.
- The platform is able to merge the inserted videos into one longer video.
cards.name: F. As a casual video editor, I want to combine many video clips into one video so that I can create a longer video as I intend to.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- Each clip is able to be rearranged in any order in the home screen.
- A clip can be dragged onto any position among the clips.
cards.name: G. As a casual video editor, I want to rearrange my clips so that I can arrange them into a specific order.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- React Native video processing library is used to apply this function.
- Videos can be trimmed into any size.
cards.name: H. As a casual video editor, I want to trim my clips so that I can remove the video parts that are not needed.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- At least 5 pre-made templates are able to be selected by a user to apply to their video project.
- The pre-made templates consist of different themes that suit different styles of video.
cards.name: J. As a person with no video editing experience, I want to make a video for a friend's birthday so that I can then send it to them.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- Able to upload the entire exported video onto Facebook, Instagram and Twitter.
- Connect the platform to social media platforms.
cards.name: I. As a professional marketer, I want to be able to push videos straight onto my social media pages so that I can promote my products and/or services.

cards.desc:
Acceptance Criteria:
- Merged videos in the platform are able to be exported into a video into mobile storage after clicking export.
- User is able to select different export quality.
